      "readmeDetail": "### 12. Use Row 3 As The Base For AdamW Diagnostic Comparisons\n\n- Rank: 12\n- Motivation: Row 2 AdamW was much slower, but its diagnostics can still explain which matrices row 3 improves.\n- Mechanism: Comparing update norms and moment statistics under AdamW vs Muon can guide per-family Muon tuning.\n- Expected benefit: 25 to 100 steps indirectly.\n- Concrete experiment: Log per-family update-to-weight RMS, weight norms, and gradient spectra under row 2 and row 3 recipes for the same seed and early steps.\n- Expected failure mode: Diagnostics may explain differences without yielding an actionable recipe change.\n- Confidence: 0.36\n- Expected step gain: 50\n\nDetailed explanation: This is not a near-term record attempt, but it may turn the AdamW control row into useful information for Muon tuning.",
