      "readmeDetail": "### 12. Try Structured Norm Constraints Beyond Whole-Matrix Frobenius Radius\n\n- Rank: 12\n- Motivation: Whole-matrix Frobenius radius is simple, but attention and MLP matrices may benefit from more local scale constraints.\n- Mechanism: Preserve row norms, column norms, head-wise norms, or spectral norm envelopes instead of only total Frobenius norm.\n- Expected benefit: Better scale distribution inside a matrix while keeping the global benefits of norm-controlled training.\n- Concrete experiment: Start with head-wise or row/column group norms for QKV and attention projection, leaving MLP matrices on Frobenius spheres.\n- Expected failure mode: More granular constraints may fight representation learning and add implementation complexity without improving validation loss.\n- Confidence: low-medium\n- Expected step gain: 0 to 75\n\nDetailed explanation:\n\nThis is a more speculative extension of the hyperball idea. I would not do it before radius and LR tuning, but it could matter if whole-matrix constraints are too coarse for QKV or attention output structure.",
