      "readmeDetail": "### 9. Use Sequential Multi-Seed Selection Instead Of One-Seed Screening\n\n- Rank: 9\n- Motivation: Row 6 shows robust evidence matters and some seeds still miss the target at 3375.\n- Mechanism: Use a staged protocol: small seed batches for screening, then expand only promising candidates.\n- Expected benefit: Reduce the chance of overfitting one seed while keeping compute manageable.\n- Concrete experiment: Screen candidates with 3 to 5 seeds, stop losers early, and promote only candidates whose confidence interval beats row 6.\n- Expected failure mode: Sequential decisions may still bias toward lucky early batches if the protocol is not fixed in advance.\n- Confidence: medium\n- Expected step gain: indirect\n\nDetailed explanation:\n\nThis is a research-process idea. The leaderboard is now in a regime where many changes will be smaller than seed variation. Taste has to include evaluation design.",
