      "readmeDetail": "### 11. Try Two-Phase NorMuonH To MuonH Or High-WD Muon\n\n- Rank: 11\n- Motivation: NorMuonH may be best early, while simpler MuonH or high-WD Muon could be better late.\n- Mechanism: Switch optimizer branch partway through training.\n- Expected benefit: Use adaptive balancing early and simpler stable dynamics near the target.\n- Concrete experiment: Switch from NorMuonH to MuonH or high-WD Muon at 60, 70, or 80 percent progress.\n- Expected failure mode: Switching geometry may create transient loss or erase the variance-state advantage.\n- Confidence: low-medium\n- Expected step gain: 0 to 50\n\nDetailed explanation:\n\nThis is speculative and should follow boundary and scalar tuning. It is a way to test whether NorMuonH's role is phase-specific.",
