      "readmeDetail": "### 12. Explore More Granular Axis Normalization\n\n- Rank: 12\n- Motivation: Short-axis variance is a compromise; attention heads or MLP blocks may prefer different grouping.\n- Mechanism: Use head-wise, block-wise, row-wise, column-wise, or mixed variance buffers.\n- Expected benefit: Better balance update energy inside structured matrices.\n- Concrete experiment: Start with head-wise QKV buffers and compare to row 8 short-axis buffers.\n- Expected failure mode: More granular normalization may overfit and add overhead.\n- Confidence: low-medium\n- Expected step gain: 0 to 50\n\nDetailed explanation:\n\nThis is a lower-priority extension. Short-axis normalization is already elegant; only diagnostics should justify finer granularity.",
