      "readmeDetail": "### 5. Split NorMuon LR and WD by Matrix Family\n\n- Rank: 5\n- Motivation: One global LR and WD is used across all hidden 2D matrices.\n- Mechanism: Q/K/V, attention projection, MLP input, and MLP projection likely need different angular and radial treatment because their shapes, roles, and variance-normalization axes differ.\n- Expected benefit: Better threshold crossing without adding new optimizer state.\n- Concrete experiment: Create per-family NorMuon groups and start with LR/WD multipliers around the row 10 global point. Promote only settings that survive matched-seed validation.\n- Expected failure mode: Added degrees of freedom overfit screening seeds and worsen n=20 evidence.\n- Confidence: 0.56\n- Expected step gain: 40\n\nDetailed explanation: Per-family grouping has been an obvious but repeatedly deferred direction. Row 10 makes it sharper because NorMuon's axis choice and WD act per matrix but are controlled globally.",
