      "readmeDetail": "### 3. Schedule the Contra Coefficient Through Training\n\n- Rank: 3\n- Motivation: The useful singular-mode weighting may differ between early feature discovery and late validation refinement.\n- Mechanism: Strong Contra early could encourage diverse small-mode exploration; weaker Contra late could avoid over-damping the dominant directions needed for convergence.\n- Expected benefit: Better final mean without sacrificing early descent.\n- Concrete experiment: Test constant Contra, warmup-to-Contra, Contra-to-zero, and late-only Contra schedules. Compare validation at 3150, 3200, and 3225.\n- Expected failure mode: Any schedule adds complexity but the constant coefficient is already near-optimal.\n- Confidence: 0.58\n- Expected step gain: 25\n\nDetailed explanation: The allowed Contra-Muon writeup also discusses Soft-Muon as another spectral shaping direction. A schedule over spectral strength is a natural next step, but it should be tested without importing any later-row claims from the repository page.",
