      "matches": [],
      "readmeDetail": "12. **Add diagnostics for spectra and basis stability.** Log pre- and post-SOAP update spectra, SOAP denominator ranges, row/column covariance eigenvalues, basis drift, floor activation rates, and per-family update-to-weight ratios.",
      "rowContext": "## Method Summary\n\nRow 14 keeps the row 11 Contra-Muon plus NorMuon-lite plus u/w-floor stack, then adds SOAP/Shampoo-basis preconditioning only to the MLP hidden matrices before the Muon orthogonalization step.\n\nThe unchanged attention path is:\n\n1. Momentum-smoothed hidden-matrix gradient.\n2. Newton-Schulz Muon orthogonalization.\n3. Contra-Muon subtraction of an operator-normalized momentum-gradient direction.\n4. Frobenius renormalization, shape scaling, row/column variance normalization, and another Frobenius renormalization.\n5. u/w-floor scaling when `||u||_F / ||w||_F < 0.35`.\n\nThe new MLP path for parameters named `mlp.fc.weight` and `mlp.proj.weight` is:\n\n1. Momentum-smoothed hidden-matrix gradient.\n2. SOAP/Shampoo-basis preconditioning in a row and column eigenbasis.\n3. Newton-Schulz Muon orthogonalization.\n4. Contra-Muon subtraction.\n5. NorMuon-lite row/column variance normalization and u/w-floor scaling.\n\nThe key scalar settings in the revealed implementation are:\n\n- `MUON_LR = 0.0375`\n- `MU = 0.95`\n- `CONTRA_MUON = 0.4`\n- `TARGET_UW = 0.35`\n- `SOAP_BETA2 = 0.90`\n- `train_steps = 3175`\n- Extra validation at `3100`, `3125`, `3150`, and `3175`\n\nThe constructor still prints `muon_weight_decay = 0.025`, but as in row 11 the revealed `Muon.step` implementation does not apply hidden weight decay. Effective hidden weight decay is zero.",
