      "readmeDetail": "## Method Summary\n\nRow 15 is a first valid Track 3 result for Newton-Muon. It starts from plain Muon plus auxiliary AdamW, then right-preconditions hidden-matrix gradients using activation covariance statistics before the usual Muon momentum and Newton-Schulz update.\n\nThe central update idea is:\n\n1. Collect input activation covariance statistics `ZZ^T` for each hidden linear layer family.\n2. Periodically form a regularized inverse covariance.\n3. Right-multiply hidden matrix gradients by that inverse covariance.\n4. Feed the preconditioned gradients into standard Muon momentum and Newton-Schulz orthogonalization.\n5. Apply decoupled weight decay and the Muon update.\n\nThe arXiv abstract frames this as a Newton-type interpretation of Muon: standard Muon can be seen as dropping the input-second-moment right preconditioner, while Newton-Muon keeps the `G(ZZ^T)^-1` term before taking the matrix sign/polar direction.",
      "sourcePath": "outputs/row_15/README.md"
