      "readmeDetail": "## Method Summary\n\nTrustlight starts from the row 14 recipe:\n\n- Contra-Muon with `CONTRA_MUON = 0.4`.\n- NorMuon-lite row/column variance normalization.\n- u/w-floor target `0.35`.\n- No effective hidden weight decay despite the stored `weight_decay=0.025`.\n- MLP SOAP/Shampoo-basis preconditioning for `mlp.fc.weight` and `mlp.proj.weight` before the Contra/NorMuon-lite path.\n\nRow 16 adds a narrow attention SOAP path only for attention output projection weights, `attn.proj.weight`. It does not apply SOAP to Q/K/V.\n\nThe attention SOAP candidate is not used directly. It is bounded and blended with the raw Nesterov-style momentum update through a trust gate:\n\n1. Compute the ordinary momentum update.\n2. Compute a SOAP-preconditioned attention-projection candidate.\n3. Clamp the SOAP denominator with a floor so tiny projected variances do not create extreme whitening.\n4. Measure whether the SOAP candidate agrees with the raw momentum direction and is sufficiently aligned with the gradient.\n5. Blend raw and SOAP directions using that trust gate.\n6. Renormalize the blended update to preserve the raw momentum update norm.\n7. Feed the result through the usual Muon/Contra/NorMuon-lite/u-w-floor stack.",
