      "rowContext": "## Method Summary\n\nRow 17 starts from the row 11 family: hidden 2D matrices use a Muon-derived optimizer with Contra-Muon and the one-sided update-to-weight floor, while embeddings, output head, and scalar/vector parameters keep auxiliary AdamW. The new ingredient is Aurora, which replaces the standard Muon polar factor with a leverage-uniform polar update for non-square matrices.\n\nThe active hidden-matrix update in the local log is:\n\n1. Maintain Muon momentum with `mu=0.95` and Nesterov-style blending.\n2. Estimate an operator-norm-normalized copy of the blended update for Contra-Muon.\n3. Apply `aurora_orthogonalize(update, pp_iterations=2, pp_beta=0.5)`.\n4. Subtract `CONTRA_MUON / 2 * normalized_grad`, with `CONTRA_MUON=0.4`.\n5. Renormalize the Contra-modified update back to the Aurora/polar Frobenius norm.\n6. Apply the standard Muon spectral aspect-ratio scale.\n7. Apply the u/w floor so `||u||_F / ||w||_F >= TARGET_UW=0.35`.\n8. Step with hidden LR `0.0375` and effective hidden weight decay `0`.\n\nThe implementation does not show the NorMuon-lite row/column variance normalizer from my row 11 memory. So for row 17 I treat the active logged path as Aurora polar plus Contra-Muon plus u/w-floor. The row text still says \"setup from #11\", and the PR frames the mechanism stack as Contra-Muon plus u/w-floor.",
