      "readmeDetail": "## Revealed Row\n\n| # | Steps to 3.28 | Evidence | Description | Date | Log | Contributors |\n| - | - | - | - | - | - | - |\n| 21 | 4100 | 3.2776 (n=4)✓ | Shampoo (`lr=0.0015`, `wd=0.2`, `betas=(.9, .95)`, `precond_freq=5`, `power=-1/4`) | 2026/05/13 | `results/20260513_shampoo_1_4_power/503575c5-6dde-425a-b461-2df4d99db974.txt` | `@kellerjordan0` |\n\n## Method Summary\n\nRow 21 is a direct Shampoo baseline for hidden 2D transformer block matrices, with the familiar auxiliary AdamW path for embeddings, output head, gains, biases, and other non-2D parameters.\n\nThe hidden optimizer is `DistributedShampoo`:\n\n```python\noptimizer2 = DistributedShampoo(\n    [p for p in model.blocks.parameters() if p.ndim >= 2],\n    lr=0.0015,\n    betas=(0.9, 0.95),\n    weight_decay=0.2,\n    weight_decay_type=WeightDecayType.DECOUPLED,\n    max_preconditioner_dim=8192,\n    precondition_frequency=5,\n    start_preconditioning_step=-1,\n    grafting_config=AdamPreconditionerConfig(beta2=0.95, epsilon=1e-10),\n    distributed_config=shampoo_distributed_config(),\n)\n```\n\nThe row text says the matrix-power setting is `power=-1/4`, matching Shampoo-style inverse fourth-root preconditioning for matrix factors.\n\nAuxiliary AdamW is unchanged from many previous rows:\n\n- embedding LR `0.3`;\n- output projection LR `1/320`;\n- scalar/vector LR `0.01`;\n- betas `(0.8, 0.95)`;\n- `eps=1e-10`;\n- no weight decay.",
