      "rowContext": "## Method Summary\n\nMuown turns each hidden 2D weight matrix into a row-wise weight-normalized representation. For a row, the optimizer stores a gain `g`, an internal direction variable `v`, and a scheduled internal norm `v_norm`, with the effective weight reconstructed as:\n\n```text\nW = g * v / ||v||\n```\n\nThe optimizer then applies different geometry to the two pieces:\n\n- the direction component receives a Muon-like Nesterov momentum update followed by Polar Express / Newton-Schulz orthogonalization;\n- the row gain `g` receives Adam-style scalar adaptation with bias correction;\n- the internal `v_norm` is scheduled toward a family-specific target, which attenuates angular movement because recomposition normalizes `v` before multiplying by `g`.\n\nThis is a more granular radial policy than prior matrix-wide Frobenius radii, decoupled weight decay, or update-to-weight floors. The radial variable is now row-level and explicitly optimized.",
      "sourcePath": "outputs/row_23/ideas.json"
