      "readmeDetail": "## Revealed Row\n\n| Row | Step | Validation | Method | Date | Evidence | Contributor |\n| - | -: | - | - | - | - | - |\n| 24 | 3175 | 3.2782 (n=10) | Setup from #11, with split LR cooldown: auxiliary AdamW `cooldown_frac=0.4` and matrix cooldown `cooldown_frac=0.8` | 2026/05/09 | `results/20260509_contra_muon_split_cooldown/c1af0bd1-6999-44d1-a618-3d1234ea32f0.txt`, PR 292 | @zhiweixx |\n\n## Method Summary\n\nRow 24 is a narrow but important schedule ablation on the row 11 Contra-Muon family. The optimizer stack is otherwise the row 11-style recipe: Contra-Muon on hidden 2D matrices, NorMuon-lite row/column variance normalization after the Muon/Contra direction, a one-sided update-to-weight floor, and auxiliary AdamW for embeddings, output head, gains, biases, and other non-hidden-matrix parameters.\n\nThe PR states that the only substantive optimizer change is the split cooldown:\n\n- auxiliary AdamW groups use `cooldown_frac = 0.4`;\n- matrix Contra-Muon/NorMuon groups use `cooldown_frac = 0.8`.\n\nUnder the linear schedule, a group stays at full LR until progress reaches `1 - cooldown_frac`, then decays linearly to zero. That means:\n\n- matrix updates begin cooling early, after 20 percent of training, and decay slowly over the final 80 percent;\n- auxiliary AdamW stays at full LR until 60 percent of training, then decays sharply over the final 40 percent.\n\nThis is not a new spectral map or new preconditioner. It is evidence that the hidden matrix optimizer and auxiliary AdamW path want different late-training temperature profiles.",
