      "readmeDetail": "### 2. Sweep Contra Strength And End Step Under Muown\n\n- Rank: 2\n- Motivation: Row 31 uses `CONTRA_MUON=0.65` and decays to normal by step `1925`.\n- Mechanism: Search the spectral correction strength and phase duration inside the row-level direction update.\n- Expected benefit: Find whether Muown wants a shorter, longer, weaker, or stronger Contra phase than ordinary Muon stacks.\n- Concrete experiment: Sweep `CONTRA_MUON` in `{0.3,0.5,0.65,0.8}` and end step in `{1500,1800,1925,2200,2500}`.\n- Expected failure mode: Strong Contra may interact badly with scheduled V-norm targets and create high-loss seeds.\n- Confidence: `0.66`\n- Expected step gain: `5` to `20`\n\nDetailed explanation: Contra's coefficient is not directly comparable across Muon and Muown because Muown updates internal directions, not raw weights. It deserves its own surface.",
