      "readmeDetail": "### 3. Family-Specific PSGD Settings\n\n- Rank: 3\n- Motivation: One global PSGD tuple is unlikely to fit Q/K/V, attention output, MLP fc, and MLP projection equally.\n- Mechanism: Split hidden matrix groups by family with separate LR, `precond_lr`, beta, schedule, and maybe Hyperball radii.\n- Expected benefit: Recovers competitiveness by adapting preconditioner speed and update size to matrix shape and role.\n- Concrete experiment: Start with MLP-only and attention-only multipliers, then split `mlp.fc` versus `mlp.proj` and Q/K/V versus attention output.\n- Expected failure mode: PSGD factor state is already shape-adaptive enough that family splitting mostly adds noise.\n- Confidence: 0.74\n- Expected step gain: 35\n\nDetailed explanation: Nearly every strong row eventually splits hidden matrices. PSGD's Kronecker factors adapt within each matrix, but that does not tune global LR or radial policy by family.",
