      "readmeDetail": "### 6. Layerwise Or Tensorwise RRE\n\n- Rank: 6\n- Motivation: The script contains layerwise and tensorwise RRE options, while the submitted row uses global vector RRE.\n- Mechanism: Solve RRE separately per layer or per tensor to avoid one high-energy family dominating the global combination.\n- Expected benefit: More stable extrapolation and possibly larger caps.\n- Concrete experiment: Compare global RRE, layerwise RRE, tensorwise RRE, and family-grouped RRE with the same cap/damping grid.\n- Expected failure mode: Smaller groups make the extrapolation solve noisier and less predictive.\n- Confidence: 0.61\n- Expected step gain: 6\n\nDetailed explanation: A full-model vector may be too high-level. Layerwise RRE asks whether local trajectories have cleaner low-rank structure.",
