      "rowContext": "## Method Summary\n\nRow 34 starts from the row 30 stack: Aurora row-balanced polar on wide `mlp.proj`, radial brake, extended Contra-Muon-to-normal ramp, MLP+V SOAP, Soft-Muon disabled, NorMuon-lite effectively disabled, and inherited power-law cooldown. The new method is a late reduced-rank extrapolation overlay on the parameter vector.\n\nThe submitted settings are:\n\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_NAME=\"rre\"`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_START_STEP=2820`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_EVERY=5`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_NUM_CHECKPOINTS=4`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_REGULARIZATION=1e-6`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_DAMPING=0.875`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_MAX_REL=0.001`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_RESET_MOMENTUM=False`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_STOP_STEP=2925`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_AFTER_STOP_EVERY=0`\n- `EXTRAPOLATION_PARAM_FILTER=\"all\"`\n- `RUN_STOP_STEP=2925`, while the inherited `train_steps` remains 3020.\n\nThe optimizer records flattened parameter vectors after the normal optimizer step. Once four checkpoints are available and the step is on the `every=5` grid, it solves the RRE combination over recent parameter differences, damps the extrapolated move, caps the extrapolation delta to at most `0.001 * ||current_parameter_vector||`, writes the extrapolated vector back into the model, and keeps optimizer momentum rather than resetting it.\n\n## Research Taste Diagnosis\n\nPromising: RRE is cheap in the benchmark's step metric. It adds no extra forward/backward passes and acts on a full-parameter trajectory, including all optimizer groups through the model state. This directly validates the idea that slow-time-scale wrappers can matter on top of strong inner optimizers.\n\nFragile: Extrapolation can easily destabilize late training. The row survives because it is late, damped, capped, and stopped. The safety controls may be the method.\n\nUndertuned: The only revealed setting is global all-parameter RRE with `k=4`, every five steps, damping `0.875`, max relative update `0.001`, and no momentum reset. It does not split by parameter family, reset policy, endpoint, or cap schedule.\n\nLikely noise: The n=8 mean passes, but p=0.168 versus row 30 means the apparent 2925 gain could be partly variance. A matched row 30 rerun or RRE on/off paired seeds should be required before strong causal claims.",
